solutions.content:
# Intuition
1) Can not use stack considering the testcase when one Domino is falling towards **Right** and one Domino is falling towards **Left**. Here we need to move half of the dominos fall Right and half fall Left in between these two dominos.
2) Whereas, rest of the dominos either continously fall Left or Right.
3) Using two pointers can handle all type of testcases


# Approach
1) The dominos group can be divided as:
   a) **. L**
   b) **. R**
   c) **L .**
   d) **R .**
   e) **L R**
   f) **R L**
   g) **L L**
   h) **R R**
2) The case where half of the in-between dominos fall left and half right comes under -> **R L** group.
3) Other groups can be handled in a **monotonous** way.
4) By using **two pointers**, we observe if the **current index** (j) is R or L, if it is R then we observe the **previous index** (i) which shows the group(from the above group table) the pointers i & j refer to.
5) So, if the pair **{ i, j }** belongs to:
 a) **. L** - run a loop from i to j and fill with 'L'
 b) **. R** - do nothing ( even if vertical dominos are in-between)
 c) **L .** - do nothing ( even if vertical dominos are in-between)
 d) **R .** - run a loop from i to j and fill with 'R'
 e) **L R** - do nothing ( even if vertical dominos are in-between)
 f) **R L** - calculate the distance between i and j to first distribute half indices to 'R' and then half indices to 'L'. If there is odd no. of spaces available, we need to skip the middle domino as it is self-balanced.
 g) **L L** - run a loop from i to j and fill with 'L'
 h) **R R** - run a loop from i to j and fill with 'R'

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
 **O(n+k) ~ O(n)**
 where **n** is for traversing the string and **k** is for traversing to fill substrings with 'L' and 'R'

- Space complexity:
**O(1)** - Since no additional space is required to store

# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    string pushDominoes(string dom) {
        int i=0,j=0,n=dom.size();
        while(i<n){
            int j=i;
            int solA = -1, solB = -1, solC = -1, solD = -1;
            while(j<n){
                if(dom[j]=='L'){
                    if(i==j){
                        j++;
                        continue;
                    }
                    if(dom[i]=='.' || dom[i]=='L'){
                        // L to be inserted to the left till i
                        solA = 1;
                        break;
                    }
                    else{
                        // half R and half L to be inserted
                        solC = 1;
                        break;
                    }
                }
                else if(dom[j]=='R'){
                     if(i==j){
                        j++;
                        continue;
                    }
                    if(dom[i]=='R'){
                        // fill R from i to j
                        solB = 1;
                        // cout<<i<<" "<<j<<endl;
                        break;
                    }
                    // move i to curr pos of j
                    i=j;
                    break;
                }
                else if(j==n-1 && dom[j]=='.'){
                    if(dom[i]=='R'){
                        solD=1;
                        break;
                    }
                }
                j++;
            }
            // cout<<endl;
            if(solA==1){
                // inserting L
                for(int k=i;k<j && k<n;k++) dom[k]='L';
            }
            if(solB==1){
                // inserting R
                for(int k=i;k<j && k<n;k++) dom[k]='R';
            }
            if(solC==1){
                int k=i+(j-i-1)/2;
                for(int z=i;z<=k && z<n;z++) dom[z]='R';
                for(int z=j;z>=(j-k+i) && z>0;z--) dom[z]='L';
            }
            if(solD==1){
                for(int z=i;z<n;z++) dom[z]='R';
            }
            i=j;
        }
        return dom;
    }
};
```

