solutions.content:
**Approach:**
So what we need to do is just focus on the dominoes which are standing upright i.e. ' . ' Now if we are at a upright domino we need to know how far is a domino towards left which was pushed right and how far is a domnio which was pushed to the left. We can do this for every domino but this makes our work easier as we can just store the required distances in two arrays.

Let's see how the algorithm works

First we walk from left to right
* If we find a domino which is pushed towards Left ' L ' we know this can never affect the dominoes on right so we mark our flag as false
* If we find a domino which is pushed towards right 'R' we know this can affect the dominoes on the right side and thus we start a fresh count from zero.
* If we find a domino which is upright we change its value to count only if there was a Right earlier to it which is indicated by flag variable.

Similarly we walk from right to left and make a similar array.

Finally we move from left to right and if we find an upright domino we check the distance of left and right domino and which ever is less we change our values accordingly.

The key point to note here is that only the values of the upright dominoes will change and thus we update our left and right arrays only at those positions.



The left and right are initialised with INT_MAX so as to account for unavalaibitiy of the required push.

C++ code:
```
class Solution {
public:
    string pushDominoes(string dominoes) {
        int n = dominoes.size();
        vector<int> left(n,INT_MAX);
        int count = 0;
        bool flag = false;
        for(int i=0;i<n;i++)
        {
            if(dominoes[i]=='L')
            {
                flag = false;
            }    
            else if(dominoes[i]=='R')
            {
                count=0;
                flag = true;
            }
            else
            {
                if(flag)
                {
                    count++;
                    left[i]=count;
                }
            }
        }
        vector<int> right(n,INT_MAX);
        flag = false;
        for(int i=n-1;i>=0;i--)
        {
            if(dominoes[i]=='R')
            {
                flag = false;
            }    
            else if(dominoes[i]=='L')
            {
                count=0;
                flag = true;
            }
            else
            {
                if(flag)
                {
                    count++;
                    right[i]=count;
                }
            }
        }
        for(int i=0;i<n;i++)
        {
            if(dominoes[i]=='.')
            {
                if(left[i]<right[i])
                    dominoes[i]='R';
                else if(left[i]>right[i])
                    dominoes[i]='L';
            }
        }
        return dominoes;
    }
};
```

