solutions.content:
Testing the various corner cases is a challenge, but a essentially I grouped the string into substrings [left, right] where _right_ is the index of the next action ('R' or 'L') and _left_ maybe an action.

Depending on the which state, the return can be `memset` for quick performance;
|dominoes[left]|dominoes[right]|result|
|---|---|---|
|`R`|`R`|Everything between _left_ and _right_ gets filled with `R` and _left_ is set to _right_|
|`.`|`R`|Everything upto _right_ gets filled with `.` and _left_ is set to _right_|
|`L`|`R`|Everything after _left_ upto _right_ gets filled with `.` and _left_ is set to _right_|
|`R`|`L`|They will meet in the middle. Fill first half with `R` then add a `.` if the gap between them is odd, before filling the rest with `L`|
|`.` or `L`|`L`|Fill _left_ to _right_ with `L` and set _left_ to just after _right_|

There is some bonus, corner cases to do with the start and end, but not too much trouble. The resulting code is not a pretty as I would like, but runs fast;

```c
char * pushDominoes(char * dominoes) {
	size_t len = strlen(dominoes);
	char* const ret = malloc(len + 1);
	ret[len] = '\0';

	int left = 0;
	while (left < len) {
		/* Find the next interesting action */
		int right = left + 1;
		while (right < len && '.' == dominoes[right]) {
			++right;
		}
		if (right == len) { /* No other movements found before the end */
			ret[left] = dominoes[left];
			memset(&ret[left + 1], ('R' == dominoes[left]) ? 'R' : '.', right - left - 1);
			break;
		} else if ('R' == dominoes[right]) {
			ret[left] = dominoes[left];
			memset(&ret[left + 1], ('R' == dominoes[left]) ? 'R' : '.', right - left - 1);
			left = right;
		} else if ('L' == dominoes[right]) { /* Dominoes will be toppling left */
			int pos = left;
			if ('R' == dominoes[left]) { /* Dominoes will be toppling right too */
				int half = (right - left + 1) / 2;
				memset(&ret[pos], 'R', half);
				pos += half;
				if (0 == (right - left) % 2) { /* Is there a domino in the middle */
					ret[pos++] = '.';
				}
			}
			memset(&ret[pos], 'L', right - pos + 1);
			left = right + 1;    
	  }
  }
  return ret;
}
```

