/* Lets take example2 to understand the concept
                             ". L . R . . . L R . . L . ."
		Firstly we'll do prefix count of how many will fall towards right and left.
		We'll maintain 2 vectors right and left.

		For right vector before that there are few considerations we need to keep in mind
		1) We'll traverse dominoes string from left to right
		2) If dominoes[i] == 'L' then it won't fall towards right so count=0 at ith index.
		3) If dominoes[i] == 'R' then it will fall towards right only so **count=1** at every ith index.
		    For example - dominoes string = "R R . R"
			                        count =  1 1 2 1
			Here, As we are considering every 'R' as a starting point of dominoes which will fall towards right
			And for now you can ignore how does 2 comes at 2nd index (We'll discuss this in next point).
			*I hope I made myself clear about this particular case*
		4) If dominoes[i] == '.' then we have to check if last index is non-zero or not. As In case 2) we have
		    non-zero value at 1st index so we'll increment value by 1. As this will also fall on right only. Otherwise
			it'll be 0 only.
			Note - Yah, there maybe case arising in your mind what if it falls on left as some dominoes maybe
			falling on left. That we'll consider once we find all the indexes with respect to 'R' dominoes.

		Similarly, For left vector before that there are few considerations we need to keep in mind
		1) We'll traverse dominoes string from right to left
		2) If dominoes[i] == 'R' then it won't fall towards left so count=0 at ith index.
		3) If dominoes[i] == 'L' then it will fall towards left only so **count=1** at every ith index.
		    For example - dominoes string = "L L . L"
			                        count =  1 1 2 1
			Here, As we are considering every 'L' as a starting point of dominoes which will fall towards left
			And for now you can ignore how does 2 comes at 2nd index (We'll discuss this in next point).
			*I hope I made myself clear about this particular case*
		4) If dominoes[i] == '.' then we have to check if last index is non-zero or not. As In case 2) we have
		    non-zero value at 3rd index so we'll increment value by 1. As this will also fall on left only. Otherwise
			it'll be 0 only.
			Note - Yah, there maybe case arising in your mind what if it falls on right as some dominoes maybe
			falling on right. That we'll consider once we find all the indexes with respect to 'L' dominoes.

		Now, coming back to example2. Here, we'll firstly find right and left vector.
		Afterwards we'll perform some operations.
		                                ". L . R . . . L R . . L . ."
								 right - 0 0 0 1 2 3 4 0 1 2 3 0 0 0
								  left - 2 1 0 0 4 3 2 1 0 3 2 1 0 0

		1) Now, if left[i]==0 && right[i]==0, it means it'll be stable So, we'll append '.' in ans.
		2) Again, if either is non-zero and another is 0 then it'll fall in favor of non-zero direction
		3) And if both are non-zero then it'll fall in favor of that direction which have a minimum
		   value at that particular index. And if both have equal values then it'll remain stable.
		   Example - if right[i]=2 and left[i]=3 then it'll fall towards right because all dominoes are
		   simultaneously falling, so domino of this particular index will fall to that direction
		   in which it has minimum value.
*/
string pushDominoes(string s) {
        int n=s.length(), cnt=1;
        vector<int> left(n), right(n);
        for(int i=0;i<n;i++) {
            if(s[i]=='R')
                cnt=1, right[i]=cnt++;
            else if((i==0 && s[i]=='.')||s[i]=='L')
                right[i]=0, cnt=1;
            else if(i!=0 && s[i]=='.' && right[i-1]!=0)
                right[i]=cnt++;
            else
                right[i]=0;
        }
        for(int i=n-1;i>=0;i--) {
            if(s[i]=='L')
                cnt=1, left[i]=cnt++;
            else if((i==n-1 && s[i]=='.')||s[i]=='R')
                left[i]=0, cnt=1;
            else if(i!=n-1 && s[i]=='.' && left[i+1]!=0)
                left[i]=cnt++;
            else
                left[i]=0;
        }
        string ans;
        for(int i=0;i<n;i++){
            if(left[i]!=0 && right[i]==0)
                ans+="L";
            else if(left[i]==0 && right[i]!=0)
                ans+="R";
            else if(left[i]==0 && right[i]==0)
                ans+=".";
            else {
                if(left[i]<right[i])
                    ans+="L";
                else if(right[i]<left[i])
                    ans+="R";
                else
                    ans+=".";
            }
        }
        return ans;
    }

