Not sure if it is a good solution, but my approach is just do simulation.
The simulation is in the while loop, every time a push do only one forward unitl there is no pushes. like the description said

"each second, each domino that is falling to the left pushes the adjacent domino on the left. Similarly, the dominoes falling to the right push their adjacent dominoes standing on the right."

```
class Solution:
    def pushDominoes(self, dominoes : str) -> str:
        dom = list(dominoes)
        ls, rs = set(), set()
        for i, c in enumerate(dom):
            if c=='L':ls.add(i)
            elif c=='R':rs.add(i)

        while ls or rs:            
            newls = set()
            for i in ls:
                if i-1>=0 and dom[i-1]=='.':
                    if (i-2) in rs:
                        rs.remove(i-2)
                    else:
                        dom[i-1]="L"
                        newls.add(i-1)

            newrs = set()
            for i in rs:
                if i+1<len(dom) and dom[i+1]==".":
                    dom[i+1]="R"
                    newrs.add(i+1)
            ls = newls
            rs = newrs

        return "".join(dom)
```

