Lets just write the cases which are acceptable

```
ae
ea  ei
ia  ie  io  iu
oi  ou
ua
```
Therefore, for any 'a' we can have 'e', 'i', 'u' as the predecessor. Lets write for each vowel
```
a --> e  i  u             dp[i][0] = dp[i-1][1] + dp[i-1][2] + dp[i-1][4]
e --> i  a                dp[i][1] = dp[i-1][2] + dp[i-1][0]
i --> e  o                dp[i][2] = dp[i-1][1] + dp[i-1][3]
o --> i                   dp[i][3] = dp[i-1][2]
u --> o  i                dp[i][4] = dp[i-1][3] + dp[i-1][2]
```

