solutions.content:
# Intuition
The problem states to count all the permutations possible of a given length of the vowels so we have to find all possible permuatations therefore we go with recursion. 

# Approach
Label vowels with indices, 0 -> a, 1 -> b & so on.
Just keep track of the last used vowel using a last parameter and do what is told in the question. At the starting we know that last used is nothing so we specify '5' as the last used parameter. When the index reaches the desired length we return 1.  
We know that there are over lapping sub problems therefore we memoize the solution. 



# Code
```
class Solution {
    int mod=1000000007;
    private long solve(int index, int n, int last, long[][] dp){
        if(index==n)
            return 1;
        if(last == 0){
            return dp[index][0] = solve(index+1,n,1,dp)%mod;
        }
        if(dp[index][last]!=-1){
            return dp[index][last];
        }
        if(last==1){
            return dp[index][1] = (solve(index+1,n,0,dp)+solve(index+1,n,2,dp))%mod;
        }
        if(last == 2){
            return dp[index][2] = (solve(index+1,n,0,dp)+solve(index+1,n,1,dp)+solve(index+1,n,3,dp)+solve(index+1,n,4,dp))%mod;
        }
        if(last == 3){
            return dp[index][3] = (solve(index+1,n,2,dp)+solve(index+1,n,4,dp))%mod;
        }
        if(last == 4){
            return dp[index][4] = solve(index+1,n,0,dp)%mod;
        }
        else{
            return solve(index+1,n,0,dp)+solve(index+1,n,1,dp)+solve(index+1,n,2,dp)+solve(index+1,n,3,dp)+solve(index+1,n,4,dp);
        }
    }
    public int countVowelPermutation(int n) {
        long[][] dp = new long[n][6];
        for(long[] arr: dp){
            Arrays.fill(arr,-1);
        }
        long ans = solve(0,n,5,dp)%mod;
        return (int)ans;
    }
}
```

